cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.GR 

This paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning to train simulated characters to imitate dynamic and acrobatic skills. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) as it involves training agents to perform tasks in a simulated environment. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques such as convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) and generative models (cs.LG) are likely to be involved in the training process. Finally, the paper may also involve graphics and visualization techniques (cs.GR) to render the simulated characters and their movements.
